[SN]TITLE[SN]
Body of missing Cumbernauld pensioner found on golf course

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The body of missing pensioner Thomas Lamb has been found on a golf course in Cumbernauld.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mr Lamb, 79, was reported missing from the Abronhill area of Cumbernauld on Saturday 2 July, shortly after his wife died.
His body was found by a member of the public on the golf course at Palacerigg Country Park at about 14:50 on Monday.
Mr Lamb's son, Stephen Lamb, described him as a "homebody" who was grieving for his wife.
Insp Phil Rose, of Police Scotland, said: "We would like to thank members of the public and local businesses for their support during this investigation.
"Our thoughts are with the family of Mr Lamb at this difficult time."
